{{Infobox Airport | name = Bobr | nativename = | nativename-a = | nativename-r = | image = | image-width = | caption = | IATA = | ICAO = | type = Military | owner = | operator = unknown | city-served = | location = Talacyn | elevation-f = 646 | elevation-m = 197 | coordinates = {{Coord|54|22|30|N|029|22|36|E|type:airport|display=inline,title}} | website = | metric-elev = | metric-rwy = | r1-number = | r1-length-f = 10499 | r1-length-m = 3200 | r1-surface = | stat-year = | stat1-header = | stat1-data = | stat2-header = | stat2-data = | footnotes = }}
'''Bobr''' (also given as '''Bobr East''') was an air base in [[Belarus]] located 20&nbsp;km west of [[Talacyn]]. It appears to have been a forward deployment field. It is now plowed under into farmland. A new major highway connecting [[Minsk]] to [[Moscow]] is just 1&nbsp;km north of the former site.
==References== *[https://web.archive.org/web/20070810210404/http://www.russianairfields.com/airfield/Bobr-East.htm RussianAirFields.com]
