to activate= |Ship sensors= |Ship EW= |Ship armament=*1 [[French 100 mm naval gun|100 mm Creusot-Loire automatic cannon]] *1 [[RIM-7 Sea Sparrow]] launcher with 8 missiles *1 MM-38 [[Exocet]] launcher with 4 missiles *1 375mm [[Bofors]] depth charge launcher *2 Ecan Type l5 torpedo tubes with 10 torpedoes |Ship armour= |Ship notes= }} |}
'''''Drazki'' (Дръзки – Daring)''' is a {{sclass-|Wielingen|frigate}} of the [[Bulgarian Navy]]. Originally constructed for the [[Belgian Navy]] as '''''Wandelaar''''', the ship was acquired by the Bulgarian Navy in 2004. The frigate is currently in active service.
==Construction and career== ''Wandelaar'' was [[Ship naming and launching|launched]] on 21 June 1977 at the Boelwerf in [[Temse]]. The frigate was later [[Ship commissioning|commissioned]] on 3 October 1978 with the [[pennant number]] F912. ''Wandelaar'' was the third ship in the ''Wielingen'' class. .
She was sold to the Bulgarian Navy in 2004. ''Wandelaar'' was refurbished and commissioned as ''Drazki'' and with the pennant number 41. In 2008 two other [[sister ship]]s, {{ship|Belgian frigate|Wielingen|F910|2}} and {{ship|Belgian frigate|Westdiep|F911|2}}, were sold to Bulgaria.
