{{unreferenced|date=August 2013}} {{Use dmy dates|date=September 2012}} {{Infobox television | show_name = Doen met 'n Miljoen! | image = | caption = | genre = [[Game show]] | creator = [[Endemol]] | presenter = [[Casper de Vries]] | country = [[South Africa]] | language = [[Afrikaans]] | num_seasons = 3 | num_episodes = 52 | company = [[Endemol]] | network = [[kykNET]] | first_aired = 19 October 2007 | last_aired = 9 January 2009 | website = https://web.archive.org/web/20090723071118/http://beta.mnet.co.za:80/fanclub/DoenmetnMiljoen/ }}
'''''Doen met 'n Miljoen!''''' ({{lang-en|italic=yes|Do with a Million!}}) is the [[South Africa]]n Afrikaans language-version of ''[[Deal or No Deal]]''. The show was premiered on 19 October 2007 on [[kykNET]] and hosted by [[Casper de Vries]].
There are 26 players, each holding a case. The one who wins the quiz round can play the game and win up to 1,000,000 [[South African rand|rand]] (about [[US$]]122,000) or down to 1 cent (about 0.12[[Cent (United States coin)|¢]]). The player selects a case, and the one holding it guesses which value from the remaining ones on board it contains, a small prize will be awarded if he/she is correct.
